1S Pass 2D Pass 2H Pass 3C Pass 3NT Pass Pass Pass
{South opens 1\S. How do you respond? 
You bid 2\d, a 2/1 force to game.  South rebids 2\h, showing a 4-card heart suit.   

You don't have 4 \Hs, nor do you have 3 \Ss. Furthermore,  you don't have stoppers in \Cs so you cannot bid NT. Since you have to keep bidding, but have no reasonable bid you can make, you bid the fourth suit, 3\C. Compare this Deal with Deal 21.
South understands that North's \C bid is Fourth-Suit-Forcing, and does not actually show \Cs. However since South does have a \C stopper he bids 3NT. In this case this turns out to be the best game contract.}

